    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Thanks for reporting @tavitohanian!\r\n\r\nMultisigWallet is no longer part of OpenZeppelin as of #328, so I will close this issue.\r\n\r\nHowever, the question is interesting, and the piece of code can be found live in [ethereum/dapp-bin](https://github.com/ethereum/dapp-bin/blob/master/wallet/wallet.sol#L343-L363). The `block.number` is acting as a nonce, so that the same parameters can be used for a multisig transaction at different moments. (We want to be able to send 1 ether to John today, and again tomorrow, and have those two transactions receive different transaction hashes.)\r\n\r\nIt is an issue if you intend to confirm an existing transaction using `execute`, but this is not the usual way to go about it. Instead, once a proposal for a transaction is submitted, the rest of the owners will use the generated hash and call `confirm` on it.",
